^B@2^Y@3^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Okay, let's talk about the philosophy of splinter bids. Splinters are designed to let you bid thin slams when you have a good fit. So, if someone splinters they are not showing extra values. They are merely showing a game forcing hand with shortness and 4+ card support. For example the auction 1H-4C only promises an opening hand, with 4+ hearts and a singleton or void in clubs. Similarly, my auction promised 16 points (game forcing with Marge's 10) 4+ hearts and a singleton club.|
