^-|HT|f|CP||FP||at|^B@2^Z@3Bridge information stays with me as long as writing on the sand at the beach. It takes only one soft wave to wash everything away. However, as I get older I become more persistent and keep writing on the sand--reviewing the material over and over. This week I have two for the price of one. The first, opening 1NT with 5-card major, is what I really dig and follow. The second, coded Jacks and Tens, which I have no place in my brain for it and only mention it here for those aspiring bridge students. Without further ado let us look at one of the boards played during Howard's recent mentoring session discussing both.|
